NMR experiments were performed on a Bruker Avance III 700 MHz spectrometer equipped with a room-temperature TXI probe (Bruker, Karlsruhe, Germany). TopSpin 3.5 (Bruker, Karlsruhe, Germany) was used for data acquisition and processing. Spectra analysis was performed using NMRFAM-SPARKY62,63. 1H and 1H-13C HSQC spectra of paenilamicin and N-acetylpaenilamicin were recorded using samples in D2O with 0.1% acetic acid-d4 at 298 K. 1H-13C HSQC spectra were recorded with acquisition times of 120 ms and 9 ms in the direct 1H and indirect 13C dimension, respectively. A delay Δ/2 of 1.72 ms was used for INEPT transfers corresponding to 1JHC of 145 Hz. Apodization of time-domain data was performed using a squared sine-bell function shifted by 90 °. The 2D data was processed by applying linear forward prediction in the indirect 13C dimension and zero filling prior to Fourier transformation. 1H chemical shifts were referenced externally using a sample of trimethylsilylpropanoic acid (TMSP-d4, Deutero GmbH, Kastellaun, Germany) in D2O with 0.1% acetic acid-d4 measured at 298 K. 13C chemical shifts were referenced indirectly using a correction factor of f13C/1H = 0.25144953064,65. Chemical shift perturbations (CSPs) were calculated using the following equation66:1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
