				\begin{document}$${{{{{\rm{CSP}}}}}}=\sqrt{{(f\times {\Delta {\delta }}_{13{{{{{\rm{C}}}}}}})}^{2}+{({\Delta {\delta }}_{1{{{{{\rm{H}}}}}}})}^{2}}$$\end{document}CSP=(f×Δδ13C)2+(Δδ1H)2where Δδ13C and Δδ1H correspond to the 13C and 1H chemical shift differences between paenilamicin B2 and N-acetylpaenilamicin B2 for each carbon-proton pair. We used a weighting factor f of 0.06 to account for the much larger chemical shift dispersion in the 13C dimension (ca. 60 ppm) compared to that in the 1H dimension (ca. 3.5 ppm).
